// useTaskGraph
// Fetches task graph state from the API and keeps it updated via real-time CustomEvents.

On mount, fetches the initial state and registers a window listener for "task_graph_updated" events.
The refresh function is also exposed so callers can manually trigger a re-fetch.

FUNCTION useTaskGraph(project, session) -> { diagram, batches, completedTasks, pendingTasks, isLoading, error, refresh }  EXPORT
  Manages state: diagram, batches, completedTasks, pendingTasks, isLoading, error.
  On mount, calls fetchTaskGraph and registers handleTaskGraphUpdate on the window.
  On unmount, removes the event listener.

---

FUNCTION fetchTaskGraph()
  Fetches /api/projects/{project}/sessions/{session}/task-graph.
  On success, updates diagram, batches, completedTasks, and pendingTasks from the response.
  On failure, sets error and logs to console.

---

FUNCTION handleTaskGraphUpdate(event)
  Receives a "task_graph_updated" CustomEvent.
  Extracts the payload and updates diagram, batches, completedTasks, and pendingTasks.
  Clears any existing error. Warns to console if the payload cannot be parsed.
